    {
      "id": "4f74bcef237438229ee63f8c123938ee995fc39b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2012-08-20 19:49:14.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(4 inline comments)\n\nThe problem with this b1_8 version of the patch is that our b1_8 code does not include the original change from b=22040 attachment 30902 which introduces the separate flock_wire_policy_data.  It does not appear correct to be  sending the OBD_CONNECT_FLOCK_OWNER from our unpatched b1_8 without actually sending the owner data.\n\nI'm fine with landing the reservation of OBD_CONNECT_FLOCK_OWNER to b1_8 (pending Johann's approval) in http://review.whamcloud.com/3723, but the client can't send this at connect time until it is actually doing the right thing.\n\nThat is one of the main benefits of using an OBD_CONNECT_* feature flag compared to checking version numbers - e.g. 1.8.5 or 1.8.7 clients may or may not have the 30902 patch applied, but if there is a proper OBD_CONNECT flag negotiation at client connection time, the server will know how to act with each client, even if there is a mix of patched/unpatched clients at the same site.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
